articles.title: Cassidy "kicked hard in the nuts" by title-ending misfortune - Motorsport.com
articles.description: Formula E championship protagonist Nick Cassidy says he was “just too nice” after a collision with Envision Racing team-mate Sebastien Buemi in the London E-Prix dashed his title hopes.
articles.content:
Cassidy entered the first of the weekends London E-Prix races 24 points behind Jake Dennis in the championship, with both title protagonists starting on the front row for Saturdays race.
